#: ../../source/production/kv_cache_events.rst:40
#: ../../source/production/kv_cache_events.rst:91
msgid ""
"You need to enable ``enable_kv_events`` for LMCache as events are not "
"generated by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/production/kv_cache_events.rst:41
msgid ""
"If running more than 1 worker in vLLM, you need to use a non-default "
"hashing algorithm (set ``pre_caching_hash_algorithm`` in LMCache) so that"
" hashes generated per worker are the same. If not then you will have "
"duplicate events for the same operation as events are generated per "
"worker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/production/kv_cache_events.rst:42
msgid ""
"LMCache sends the events to vLLM for publishing. To enable events to be "
"published, you need to set the vLLM configuration setting ``--kv-events-"
"config``. See `vLLM KV Events configuration "
"<https://docs.vllm.ai/en/stable/api/vllm/config/kv_events/>`_ for more "
"details."
msgstr ""

